==English==

===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''kakos'': bad + daimon: spirit. [[κακοδαιμων]] from [[κακος]] ‘bad’ + [[δαιμων]] ‘genius, divinity’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kækə'di:mən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an evil or [[malevolent]] spirit as opposed to [[agathodemon]] (a good spirit). Cacodaemons are shape shifters.  There are apparently 1024 of them.
#The twelfth [[astrological]] House, from which only evil prognostics are alleged to proceed.
#(Obsolete). A [[nightmare]].
:http://www.occultopedia.com/c/cacodaemon.htm - 129k -

